<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 6:22AM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...PATCHY FOG ACROSS THE SANDHILLS THROUGH 9 AM...
Fog has developed across portions of the Sandhills, with
visibilities ranging from a half mile to a mile from Fayetteville
to Wadesboro. This will result in potentially hazardous driving
conditions this morning.
Use caution if driving this morning, as visibilities may decrease rapidly
over short distances. Leave plenty of distance between your
vehicle and the vehicle in front of you. Visibilities should
improve after 9 AM.</description>
